
  gstreamer-mediasdk
  MediaSDK support to GStreamer

Overview
--------

gstreamer-mediasdk consists in a collection of MediaSDK based plugins for
GStreamer.

  * `mfxdecode' is used to decode H.264 AVC, MPEG-2, HEVC, VC-1,
    JPEG videos using the underlying hardware capabilities. 

  * `mfxsink' is used to render the decoded frame to an Wayland
    display.
  

Features
--------

  * Decode H264 AVC, MPEG-2, JPEG, VC-1 and HEVC Videos
  * Support for the Wayland display server
  * Support for headless decode pipelines


Requirements
------------

Software requirements

  * MediaSDK 2016 R1 for Yocto Embedded (MediaSDK2016R1forYoctoEmbedded-Alpha2.tar.gz)
  * GStreamer 1.4.x (up to including GStreamer 1.6):
  * GStreamer-Plugins-Base 1.4.x (up to including GStreamer 1.6):
  * CMake
  
  * Renderers:
	  Wayland (>=1.7)

Hardware requirements

  * Intel Apollo Lake
  * Intel Braswell
  * Intel Skylake

Compiling
---------

GStreamer-MediaSDK uses CMake build tool to build the libraries.
Create build directory within then source directory and run the CMake
command to configure the build.

	mkdir -p build
	cd build
	cmake "Unix Makefiles" ../
	
Next step is to build GStreamer-MediaSDK:

	make

To install the plugin:

    make install

The plugin will be install in /opt/gst-msdk directory.

Usage
-----

  Check if GST_PLUGIN_PATH is exported with value /opt/gst-msdk.
  If not, export the environment variable.

  export GST_PLUGIN_PATH=/opt/gst-msdk

  * Play an H.264 video with an MP4 container
  $ gst-launch-1.0 filesrc location=/path/to/video.mp4 ! \
      qtdemux ! h264parse !mfxdecode ! mfxsink
